Class Album

java.lang.Object
Album
public class Album extends Object
The Album class is used to create album object which represent the properties of an album and includes logic to verify that the property values are valid.

  • Constructor Details

    • Album

      public Album(int id, String name, String artistName, String genre, int userRating, int trackCount, int runtime)
      This is the main constructor used to create an Album object.
      Parameters:
      id - The integer ID of the album within the DB. This value must be positive.
      name - The String name of the album. This value cannot be null or whitespace.
      artistName - The String artist name of the album. This value cannot be null or whitespace.
      genre - The String genere of the album. This value cannot be null or whitespace.
      userRating - The Integer rating of the album between 0 and 10.
      trackCount - The Integer number of tracks on the album. This value must be positive.
      runtime - The runtime of the album in Integer seconds. This value must be positive.
